## Callbacks

Instead of `String name = await downloadName();`, you attach the `.then()` method directly to the `Future` returning function.

```dart
void main() {
  // This DOES NOT pause main!
  downloadName().then((String name) {
    print('The name just arrived: $name');
  });

  print('Fetching data in the background...');
}
```
It might print "Fetching data..." FIRST, and then 3 seconds later print "The name just arrived"!
